    • Class com.edugility.nomen.NameValue extends AbstractValued implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • atomic

          Boolean atomic
          Whether this NameValue is considered to be atomic—i.e. not a template in need of further interpolation, but just a simple textual value.

          This field may be null.

          Design Notes

          This field is a Boolean and not a boolean so that its initial setting via the NameValue.setAtomic(boolean) method can be tracked. It is not final only so that this class may be used as a JPA entity.

          See Also:
          NameValue.isAtomic(), NameValue.setAtomic(boolean)

        • whitespaceReplacement

          String whitespaceReplacement
          A String that will replace one or more consecutive occurrences of whitespace characters in a non-atomic NameValue.

          This field may be null in which case no whitespace replacement will occur.

          See Also:
          NameValue.getWhitespaceReplacement(), NameValue.setWhitespaceReplacement(String)

        • whitespaceReplacementSet

          boolean whitespaceReplacementSet
          Indicates whether the NameValue.whitespaceReplacement field has been set via the NameValue.setWhitespaceReplacement(String) method or not.
          See Also:
          NameValue.setWhitespaceReplacement(String)
